.SH NAME
Net::Nostr::Reaction \- NIP\-25 reactions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IX Header "SYNOPSIS"
.Vb 1
\&    use Net::Nostr::Reaction;
\&
\&    # Like a note (default content is +)
\&    my $reaction = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->react(
\&        event     => $note,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Dislike
\&    my $reaction = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->react(
\&        event     => $note,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&        content   => \*(Aq\-\*(Aq,
\&    );
\&
\&    # Emoji reaction
\&    my $reaction = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->react(
\&        event     => $note,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&        content   => "\ex{1F44D}",
\&    );
\&
\&    # Custom emoji reaction (NIP\-30)
\&    my $reaction = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->react(
\&        event     => $note,
\&        pubkey    => $my_pubkey,
\&        relay_url => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&        content   => \*(Aq:soapbox:\*(Aq,
\&        emoji     => [\*(Aqsoapbox\*(Aq, \*(Aqhttps://gleasonator.com/emoji/Gleasonator/soapbox.png\*(Aq],
\&    );
\&
\&    # React to external content (kind 17)
\&    my $reaction = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->react_external(
\&        pubkey  => $my_pubkey,
\&        content => "\ex{2B50}",
\&        tags    => [
\&            [\*(Aqk\*(Aq, \*(Aqweb\*(Aq],
\&            [\*(Aqi\*(Aq, \*(Aqhttps://example.com\*(Aq],
\&        ],
\&    );
\&
\&    # Parse reaction from an event
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->from_event($event);
\&    if ($info) {
\&        say $info\->is_like ? "Liked" : $info\->content;
\&    }
\&
\&    # Validate a reaction event
\&    Net::Nostr::Reaction\->validate($event);
.Ve
.SH DESCRIPTION
.IX Header "DESCRIPTION"
Implements NIP\-25 reactions. A reaction is a kind 7 event used to react to
other nostr events. The content field indicates the reaction value:
\&\f(CW\*(C`+\*(C'\fR or empty string for a "like", \f(CW\*(C`\-\*(C'\fR for a "dislike", or an emoji
(including NIP\-30 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/30.md>
custom emoji) for an emoji reaction. Emoji reactions SHOULD NOT be
interpreted as likes or dislikes.
.PP
Tags include an \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag with the reacted event\*(Aqs ID (MUST), a \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag
with the author\*(Aqs pubkey (SHOULD), a \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag with the stringified kind
(MAY), and for addressable events an \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag with the event coordinate
(SHOULD). The \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tags SHOULD include relay and pubkey hints.
The \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag SHOULD include a relay hint. If multiple \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tags
are present, the target event\*(Aqs ID and pubkey should be last.
.PP
External content reactions (websites, podcasts, etc.) use kind 17 with
NIP\-73 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/73.md>
\&\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tags instead of \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tags.
.SH CONSTRUCTOR
.IX Header "CONSTRUCTOR"
.SS new
.IX Subsection "new"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->new(%fields);
.Ve
.PP
Creates a new \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Reaction\*(C'\fR object.  Typically returned by
"from_event"; calling \f(CW\*(C`new\*(C'\fR directly is useful for testing or
manual construction.
.PP
.Vb 4
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->new(
\&        event_id => \*(Aqaa\*(Aq x 32,
\&        content  => \*(Aq+\*(Aq,
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Accepted fields: \f(CW\*(C`event_id\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`relay_url\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`author_pubkey\*(C'\fR,
\&\f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`reacted_kind\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`event_coordinate\*(C'\fR.
Croaks on unknown arguments.
.SH "CLASS METHODS"
.IX Header "CLASS METHODS"
.SS react
.IX Subsection "react"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->react(
\&        event      => $original_event,    # Net::Nostr::Event to react to
\&        pubkey     => $hex_pubkey,        # reactor\*(Aqs hex pubkey
\&        relay_url  => \*(Aqwss://relay.example.com\*(Aq,
\&        content    => \*(Aq+\*(Aq,                # optional, default \*(Aq+\*(Aq
\&        emoji      => [\*(Aqname\*(Aq, \*(Aqurl\*(Aq],    # optional, NIP\-30 custom emoji
\&        created_at => time(),             # optional, passed to Event
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 7 reaction Net::Nostr::Event. The \f(CW\*(C`event\*(C'\fR parameter is
the Net::Nostr::Event being reacted to. The \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR is the reactor\*(Aqs
hex public key.
.PP
The content defaults to \f(CW\*(C`+\*(C'\fR (like). Pass \f(CW\*(C`\-\*(C'\fR for dislike, an emoji for
emoji reaction, or a \f(CW\*(C`:shortcode:\*(C'\fR with the \f(CW\*(C`emoji\*(C'\fR parameter for a
NIP\-30 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/30.md> custom
emoji reaction.
.PP
Returns a Net::Nostr::Event with kind 7 and the appropriate tags.
.PP
Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`event\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`relay_url\*(C'\fR is missing.
.SS react_external
.IX Subsection "react_external"
.Vb 8
\&    my $event = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->react_external(
\&        pubkey  => $hex_pubkey,
\&        content => "\ex{2B50}",
\&        tags    => [
\&            [\*(Aqk\*(Aq, \*(Aqweb\*(Aq],
\&            [\*(Aqi\*(Aq, \*(Aqhttps://example.com\*(Aq],
\&        ],
\&    );
.Ve
.PP
Creates a kind 17 external content reaction Net::Nostr::Event. The
\&\f(CW\*(C`tags\*(C'\fR must include NIP\-73 <https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/73.md>
\&\f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR and \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tags to reference the external content.
.PP
Returns a Net::Nostr::Event with kind 17.
.PP
Croaks if \f(CW\*(C`pubkey\*(C'\fR, \f(CW\*(C`content\*(C'\fR, or \f(CW\*(C`tags\*(C'\fR is missing.
.SS from_event
.IX Subsection "from_event"
.Vb 1
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->from_event($event);
.Ve
.PP
Parses reaction structure from a kind 7 or kind 17 Net::Nostr::Event.
Returns a \f(CW\*(C`Net::Nostr::Reaction\*(C'\fR object with accessors, or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR if
the event is not a reaction kind.
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    my $info = Net::Nostr::Reaction\->from_event($event);
\&    say $info\->is_like ? "Liked" : $info\->content;
.Ve
.SS validate
.IX Subsection "validate"
.Vb 1
\&    Net::Nostr::Reaction\->validate($event);
.Ve
.PP
Validates that a Net::Nostr::Event is a well\-formed NIP\-25 reaction.
Croaks if:
.IP \(bu 4
Kind is not 7 or 17
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 7 missing \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag
.IP \(bu 4
Kind 17 missing \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`i\*(C'\fR tags
.PP
.Vb 2
\&    eval { Net::Nostr::Reaction\->validate($event) };
\&    warn "Invalid reaction: $@" if $@;
.Ve
.SH "INSTANCE METHODS"
.IX Header "INSTANCE METHODS"
.SS is_like
.IX Subsection "is_like"
.Vb 1
\&    $info\->is_like;  # true for \*(Aq+\*(Aq or \*(Aq\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the reaction content is \f(CW\*(C`+\*(C'\fR or an empty string.
.SS is_dislike
.IX Subsection "is_dislike"
.Vb 1
\&    $info\->is_dislike;  # true for \*(Aq\-\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
Returns true if the reaction content is \f(CW\*(C`\-\*(C'\fR.
.SH ACCESSORS
.IX Header "ACCESSORS"
These are available on objects returned by "from_event".
.SS event_id
.IX Subsection "event_id"
.Vb 1
\&    my $id = $info\->event_id;
.Ve
.PP
The ID of the reacted event (from the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR for kind 17.
.SS relay_url
.IX Subsection "relay_url"
.Vb 1
\&    my $url = $info\->relay_url;
.Ve
.PP
The relay URL hint (from the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS author_pubkey
.IX Subsection "author_pubkey"
.Vb 1
\&    my $pk = $info\->author_pubkey;
.Ve
.PP
The pubkey of the reacted event\*(Aqs author (from the \f(CW\*(C`e\*(C'\fR or \f(CW\*(C`p\*(C'\fR tag), or
\&\f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS content
.IX Subsection "content"
.Vb 1
\&    my $c = $info\->content;  # \*(Aq+\*(Aq, \*(Aq\-\*(Aq, emoji, or \*(Aq:shortcode:\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
The reaction content.
.SS reacted_kind
.IX Subsection "reacted_kind"
.Vb 1
\&    my $kind = $info\->reacted_kind;  # \*(Aq1\*(Aq or \*(Aqweb\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
The stringified kind of the reacted event (from the \f(CW\*(C`k\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR.
.SS event_coordinate
.IX Subsection "event_coordinate"
.Vb 1
\&    my $coord = $info\->event_coordinate;  # \*(Aq30023:pubkey:d\-tag\*(Aq
.Ve
.PP
The event coordinate (from the \f(CW\*(C`a\*(C'\fR tag), or \f(CW\*(C`undef\*(C'\fR. Only present when
reacting to addressable events.
